  "poem": {
    "content": "The doctor, he called me innocent,\na fringe of doubt still clinging near.\nI saw a pyramid of honeyed events,\nclarity both false and dear.\n\nHe watched me pack the olive oil,\ntold me to run, run far away.\nA worn-out van, my shifting soil,\nto claim a different kind of day.\n\nMy heart a prison, locked and tight,\nI crouch within its shadowed walls.\nInhale the coming of the night,\nanswering freedom's distant calls.\n\nWe were together, once, you see,\nacross the fields, our laughter flowed.\nBut home is just a memory,\na stolen innocence bestowed.\n\nNow I must run, and keep on running,\nbeyond the edge, beyond the scene.\nEscaped the life I was becoming,\nforever altered, evergreen.",
